AGI -&nbsp;The Israel conference scheduled in the State in Milan for next May 7 and canceled for security issues was rescheduled in June. Walker Meghnagi, president of the Jewish Community of Milan, said. "Unfortunately - he explains - from last October 7 we live as Jews a very difficult period. We are attacked on all fronts both media and political, as well as on the streets of our city (see last episode on April 25). Unlike the propal counterpart to which everything seems to be granted, despite the methods that nothing has of democratic and pluralist. That time we have the opportunity to express our reasons, we are often banned by propal militants. And when we can express ourselves, we must do so in circumstances that require a strong presence of law enforcement. The last example is these days when we had to postpone our conference organized at the State for Tuesday, May 7. This, however, - it says - did not discourage us from reproposing it with the same palimpsest in June, also guaranteeing the participation of the same panel of speakers and in the hope that it is a more serene and with less intolerance. In this regard - he concludes - we want to offer our most felt thanks to the organizers and Prefect Claudio Sgaraglia and to the Giuseppe Petronzi. &nbsp;
<br> "It seems to be back in time - it is the comment of the president of the association Italy Israel of Savona, Cristina Franco, who had organized the meeting together with the Milanese association Pro Israel of Alessandro Litta Modignani -. When it is said to me that it seems to be in '68 I say that it seems instead of living in '38 because this is the climate that is breathing, but we must not absolutely close in our shell. We need to be on the field because we can't accept the blackmail of violence and bully."
&nbsp;
For President Franco, "accepting it today means accepting it forever and we are not willing to tolerate it", he observed. "We renounce the conference of May 7, but we do not give up proposing it again as soon as the conditions make it possible. At the time when there are problems of public danger with 100 people and 12 speakers I cannot act differently." In reference to some exponents of the movement "change route", which defined the cancellation of the conference a "victory", the president of the association adds: "It's a victory for them, but it's actually a huge defeat because it means the supposed ideals that actually carry on are fake because if they were real they would give freedom of speech." "They talk about discrimination when they're actually their first to practice it. Are they someone's puppets?" he concludes.
&nbsp;
The conference on Israel that had to be held on May 7 "was cancelled because we could not do otherwise - explains the same Litta Modignani -, but we are strongly willing to reiterate this conference as soon as the safety conditions will be guaranteed both from the State University of Milan and from the Questura of Milan. In the weeks since this event had already undergone several changes. In theory it had to last all a day, then it had been reduced to half a day, it had to be in via Festa del Perdono then it was moved to via Sant'Antonio and in the end, when they proposed to keep it only online, we refused "because "it would obviously be a smack" and an "untolerant renunciation. At that point - he continues - with a crescendo of alarms until the morning of yesterday when the university told us that our conference was classified as at very high risk we exercised our sense of responsibility" and with "many bitterness we had to give up".
Alessandro Litta Modignani "is creating a very bad and dangerous climate because it is creating a potentially violent climate of intolerance that then flows into prevarication and violence," he said. "Of course we hope that this will not happen, but the episodes we have seen over the past few months are linked by creating a climate of possible return to political violence." And "it's something everyone and not just Jews should be worried about." &nbsp;

